 succeeded in 0ms:
   460	- Pre-create a stale cidfile, spawn another wrap with the SAME path,
   461	  assert `docker run --cidfile` errors. Then call `cleanup_cidfile`
   462	  first and assert spawn succeeds. Proves the cidfile reuse rule.
   463	- Spawn a container, kill the local docker-run client with SIGKILL,
   464	  assert the container is still running (worst case pre-fix), then
   465	  call `kill_via_cidfile` and assert the container is gone.
   466	- `reap_orphaned_containers`: pre-spawn a container with the right
   467	  labels but detached + sleeping, call reap, assert it's gone.
   468	
   469	### E.3 Smoke (`reference/compose/healthcheck/smoke-subprocess-docker.sh`)
   470	
   471	Same end-state assertions as `smoke-subprocess.sh`:
   472	- ≥3 `trial.integrated`,
   473	- ≥9 `task.completed`,
   474	- ≥3 plan-task `task.completed`.
   475	
   476	Plus one new assertion specific to the new path:
   477	- After the orchestrator exits, run
   478	  `docker ps -aq --filter label=eden.host=<each-worker-hostname>`
   479	  for each subprocess-mode service and assert empty (no leftover
   480	  containers).
   481	
   482	A second smoke variant `smoke-subprocess-docker-orphan.sh` (or an
   483	inline section in the same script — TBD) kills the implementer-
   484	host container mid-experiment, brings it back up, and asserts the
   485	experiment still completes (with one fewer trial — the killed one
   486	recovers via the chunk-1 expired-claim sweeper). Proves
   487	`reap_orphaned_containers` actually reaps. **If this is too
   488	expensive for CI, fall back to a unit-level test that simulates
   489	the orphan via a pre-spawned labeled container.** Decision at
   490	impl time; document outcome in the chunk delta.
   491	
   492	## F. Verification
   493	
   494	1. `uv run pytest reference/services/_common/tests` — unit tests
   495	   pass (including new `test_container_exec.py`).
   496	2. `bash reference/compose/healthcheck/smoke-subprocess.sh` — host
   497	   mode still green.
   498	3. `bash reference/compose/healthcheck/smoke-subprocess-docker.sh`
   499	   — new docker-mode smoke green locally.
   500	4. `bash reference/compose/healthcheck/e2e.sh` and `smoke.sh` —
   501	   unchanged (host mode).
   502	5. `npx markdownlint-cli2 …` — markdown is clean.
   503	6. `uv run ruff check .` and `uv run pyright` — Python clean.
   504	7. CI (PR): all 10 existing jobs green; new
   505	   `compose-smoke-subprocess-docker` green.
   506	
   507	## G. Out of scope for this sub-chunk
   508	
   509	- **Network policy on subprocess containers** — `--network` is
   510	  default. Operators who want network egress restricted set it via
   511	  the experiment image or compose override.
   512	- **Resource limits** (`--memory` / `--cpus` / `--pids-limit`).
   513	  Same: operator-configured via the image or compose override.
   514	- **Non-root execution inside the subprocess container.** The
   515	  default `eden-runtime:dev` image runs as root; experiments that
   516	  want a non-root uid set `USER` in their experiment Dockerfile.
   517	- **DinD instead of DooD.** The wrap shape is the same; only the
   518	  daemon socket origin differs. Out of scope.
   519	- **Hardening the DooD security boundary** (sysbox, Kata, per-
   520	  worker daemons). Out of scope; documented as the reference
   521	  posture.
   522	- **Sub-chunk B (Gitea-as-actual-git-remote).** Independent plan;
   523	  this work doesn't change how implementers reach the bare repo.
   524	- **Updating branch protection to require
   525	  `compose-smoke-subprocess-docker`.** Same posture chunks 10a /
   526	  10b / 10c / 10d / 10e took for newly-added compose jobs: ship
   527	  the job, watch a few clean runs, then promote in a follow-up.
   528	
   529	## H. Risks / things to watch
   530	
   531	- **Mount-target collision with worker host's own cwd.** If a
   532	  worker host's cwd happens to fall outside any forwarded mount,
   533	  the spawned child sees an empty `cwd`. This isn't possible in
   534	  the planned compose deployment (every cwd is on a forwarded
   535	  mount), but the wrap should reject such configs at build time
   536	  for safety: `wrap_command` validates that `cwd_target` falls
   537	  under at least one mount target, and raises `ValueError`
   538	  otherwise.
   539	- **Stale containers on host crash.** Mitigated by the
   540	  `eden.host=<hostname>` label + startup-time
   541	  `reap_orphaned_containers`. Cidfile dir is host-side mounted so
   542	  cidfiles survive worker-host restart.
   543	- **`docker run --cidfile` errors on existing path.** Cidfile paths
   544	  are unique-per-spawn (uuid suffix); never reused. The reaper
   545	  best-effort-removes orphaned cidfiles whose container is gone.
   546	- **`bash -lc` and login-shell side effects.** A user's `~/.bashrc`
   547	  may fail in a fresh container (no home dir). Mitigation:
   548	  `eden-runtime:dev` ships an empty `/root/.bashrc`. Experiment
   549	  images that override `USER` should likewise.
   550	- **DooD security boundary is soft.** Documented in §D.5 and §7 of
   551	  the reference-binding chapter and called out in AGENTS.md as a
   552	  review checkpoint.
   553	- **macOS Docker Desktop GID quirk.** The docker socket inside the
   554	  Linux VM that Desktop runs has a Linux gid (often 0 for root, or
   555	  a desktop-specific gid). The `stat -f` fallback handles macOS-
   556	  side reads from the user's perspective; the in-container side
   557	  uses whatever gid is on the *bind-mounted* socket inside the
   558	  worker. setup-experiment computes that gid from inside a brief
   559	  `docker run --rm -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock
   560	  alpine stat -c '%g' /var/run/docker.sock`-style probe — yields
   561	  the gid the worker container will see, which is exactly what
   562	  `group_add` needs.

